data.title: Archduchess Eleonore of Austria
data.text:
Archduchess Eleonore of Austria (2 November 1534 – 5 August 1594) was Duchess of Mantua by marriage to William I, Duke of Mantua. She was the daughter of Ferdinand I, Holy Roman Emperor and Anna of Bohemia and Hungary.

Marriage[edit]

On 26 April 1561, she married William I, Duke of Mantua.

Issue[edit]

Vincent I, Duke of Mantua (21 September 1562 – 9 February 1612) married Eleonora de' Medici.

Margherita Gonzaga (27 May 1564 – 6 January 1618) married Alfonso II d'Este.

Anna Caterina Gonzaga (17 January 1566 – 3 August 1621) married Ferdinand II, Archduke of Austria.

Titles[edit]

2 November 1534 – 26 April 1561 Archduchess Eleonore of Austria.

26 April 1561 – 14 August 1587 The Duchess of Mantua.

14 August 1587 – 5 August 1594 The Dowager Duchess of Mantua.
